HEADWORD: Colocasia
<hw>Colocasia</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a small genus of perennial
tuberous herbs of the arum family, of tropical Asia and the Pacific
islands, including the <stype>taro</stype> (<spn>Colocasia
esculente</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
